{
  "texts": [
    "TP (True Positive) refers to the number of entities accurately identified by the model.",
    "FP (False Positive) refers to instances where the model incorrectly classifies non-entities as entities.",
    "FN (False Negative) denotes the number of actual entities that the model fails to accurately identify.",
    "All models were assessed on the same test set, which was randomly selected from the Medical Cases of Wang Zhongqi.",
    "The test set contains 200 annotated sentences, covering entity types such as symptoms, pathogenesis, and treatment principles."
  ]
}